Kotte migrations (ROADMAP B7).

Migrations target a user-supplied Apache AGE database. See
`../../docs/MIGRATIONS.md` for the full operator guide, including:

  * Why alembic is operator tooling (not a runtime hook).
  * How the connection URL is resolved from DB_* env vars.
  * The relationship to `scripts/migrate_add_indices.py`
    (complementary, not redundant).
  * How to add a new migration (`make migrate-new MSG="..."`).

Everything is raw SQL via `op.execute(...)` — we intentionally don't
use SQLAlchemy metadata or `--autogenerate` because the app has no ORM
layer and every table we create must carry the `kotte_` prefix so it
can't collide with the user's own schema.
